<subSubSection box="[151,285,1328,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,627,1291,1354]" box="[151,285,1328,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<figureCitation box="[151,285,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2A–2D</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1400,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is tentatively placed in the 
<emphasis box="[781,909,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Tanytrichia</emphasis>
subgenus of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kelley, R. W." box="[1057,1214,1400,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" pagination="435 - 463" refId="ref2542" refString="Kelley, R. W. (1984) Phylogeny, morphology and classification of the micro-caddisfly genus Oxyethira Eaton (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 110, 435 - 463." type="journal article" year="1984">Kelley (1984)</bibRefCitation>
due to segment VII lacking an apicomesal ventral process; segment VIII lacking dorsolateral processes and having its venter excised to the anterior margin; segment IX venter being elongate, protruding anteriorly into segment VI; subgenital processes being fused distomesally; and aedeagus having 2 long, lateral processes beginning at midlength. The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neto &amp; Passos" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,501,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="librina" subGenus="Tanytrichia">
<emphasis box="[151,263,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Oxyethira</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[280,408,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Tanytrichia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[425,501,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">librina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Harris &amp; Davenport 1999" authorityName="Harris &amp; Davenport" authorityYear="1999" box="[729,1138,1544,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hozosa">
<emphasis box="[729,842,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">O. hozosa</emphasis>
Harris &amp; Davenport 
<quantity box="[1082,1138,1544,1570]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07746" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="1999.0">1999</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in segment IX having one narrow process posteroventrally in lateral and ventral views. However, in the new species that process in ventral view is produced into a long mesoventral process with a subapical constriction and a rounded apex while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harris &amp; Davenport" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hozosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">O. hozosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that process is a pair of finger-like mesoventral processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1688,1714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,409,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Male</emphasis>
. Length of each forewing 1.55 mm (n = 6). Head unmodified, with 3 ocelli; antennae broken and lost. Tibial spurs 1,3,4. Dorsum of head dark brown with pale yellow setae; thorax dark brown dorsally, light brown ventrally, with pale yellow setae dorsally; leg segments with light brown setae. Forewing venation typical of the genus, covered with fine yellow setae and small scattered patches of dark brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1400,2039]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,384,1832,1858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Male Genitalia.</emphasis>
Abdominal segment VII annular, without apicomesal ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1264,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Segment VIII in lateral view with posteroventral margins oblique and produced caudad (
<figureCitation box="[986,1076,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view anterior margin slightly convex, posterior margin difficult to define (
<figureCitation box="[765,857,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); in ventral view anterior margin slightly convex, posterior margin deeply excised mesally (
<figureCitation box="[625,715,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Segment IX in lateral view tapering anteriorly and withdrawn into segments VII–VIII, extending slightly beyond anterior margin of segment VII, posterior margin with five slender caudad processes, one pair dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[620,707,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, dp), another pair mesal (
<figureCitation box="[986,1073,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, mp), and one unpaired posterior mesoventral (
<figureCitation box="[301,387,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, mvp); in dorsal view, dorsal processes digitate, reaching posterior margin of tergum X (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1432,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, dp), mesal processes longer, digitate, and slightly convergent apically (
<figureCitation box="[940,1027,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, mp); in ventral view lateral margins slightly sinuous, anterior margin almost straight, posterior mesoventral process as long as inferior appendages, with subapical constriction and rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[626,713,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
, mvp). Tergum X in lateral view membranous, vertically oblong (
<figureCitation box="[159,250,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view posterior margin shallowly incised mesally (
<figureCitation box="[936,1025,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages in lateral view sclerotized, tapering apically (
<figureCitation box="[498,590,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, ia); in ventral view broad basally, tapering to blunt apices (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1385,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
, ia). Subgenital process membranous, in lateral view tapering apically, protruding below inferior appendages (
<figureCitation box="[1342,1431,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, sg); in dorsal view produced into pair of mesal processes with lateral setae (
<figureCitation box="[991,1078,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, sg). Bilobed processes digitate, each with spine-like apical seta, visible only in lateral view (dotted lines in 
<figureCitation box="[998,1086,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
, bp). Phallus tubular, smoothly curved about 45° in middle, in lateral view apical half membranous tapering to acute apex, with sclerotized, upturned and acute basal process (
<figureCitation box="[424,512,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
, sp; paired); in dorsal view fixed to dorsum of segment IX by pair of lateral sinuous apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[267,350,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
and dotted lines in 
<figureCitation box="[568,654,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, ap), acute apex with a pair of sclerotized lateral process (
<figureCitation box="[1298,1383,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,644,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-244@3.[151,1436,633,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oxyethira librina sp. nov. male genitalia. 2A, left lateral; 2B, dorsal; 2C, ventral; 2D, phallus, left lateral; 2E, phallus apex, dorsal. ap = apodeme (paired), bp = bilobed process (paired), dp = dorsal process (paired), ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process (paired), mvp = posterior mesoventral process, sg = subgenital plate, sp = sclerotized process (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
, sp); ejaculatory duct not visible.
</paragraph>
