<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The term “librina”, a noun used in apposition, refers to the oral word used by inhabitants of 
<collectingRegion box="[1340,1436,330,356]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="4" pageNumber="30">Roraima</collectingRegion>
states to designate a light rain falling on the vegetation.
</paragraph>
